claim.claim-text:
1. A hinge for a foldable bicycle comprising: 
a first plate having a first side and a second side, a notch laterally is defined in a middle portion and an ear with a through hole laterally extending out from a lower end of the second side of the first plate and directing to the second plate; 
a second plate comprising a first side pivotally attached to the first side of the first plate and a second side, and including: 
a recess laterally defined in the second side of the second plate, the recess corresponding to the groove in the second side of the first plate and dividing the second side of the second plate into an upper portion and a lower portion; 
a cavity longitudinally defined in the upper portion; 
a hole defined in and extending through the lower portion, the hole axially aligning with the cavity and aligning with the locking hole in the ear after the first plate and the second plate abutting each other; and 
a lock bolt having two opposite ends respectively rotatably received in the cavity and the hole in the second side of the second plate; 

a quick release device attached to the lock bolt, the quick release device having an actuated rod extending into the recess of the second plate and secured on the lock bolt; 
wherein the improvement comprises: 
the lock bolt rotated and extending to insert into the locking hole in the ear in the second side of the second plate by means of a drive element and a guiding element respectively on the second plate and the lock bolt when the actuated rod of the quick release device is moved to be received in the groove in the second side of he first plate.
